1. Open file and read field

(full name)   --input <input file> 
(short name)  -if     <input file> 

		format <input file> == <string>


2. Open file and write field

(full name)   --output <output file> 
(short name)  -o       <output file>

		format <output file> == <string>


3. Count iterations for field

(full name)   --iterations <iteration count> 
(short name)  -ic          <iteration count>

		format <iteration count> == <int>


4. Sizing field

(full name)   --field <x> <y>
(short name)  -f      <x> <y>

		format <x> <y> == <int> <int> 


5. Help

(full name)   --help 
(short name)  -h


6. Rule M

	-m <m>

	format <m> == <int> 


7. Rule N

	-n <n>

	format <n> == <int> 


8. Rule K

	-k <k>

	format <k> == <int>